On his return to Rome, Caesar found Pompey, who had just comÎ‡ pleted the Mithridatic war in the Rast, and was arranging for his triumphal entry into the city, at varianae with the senate. Caesar at once saw his opportunity, he formed a political coalition with Pompey and Crassus, one part of the bargain being that Caesar should have the consulship for the next year (ac. 59), and after that the govern- ment of Gaul for five years. In accordance with this programme, Caesar was entrusted, at the expiration of his consulship, with the command of Cisalpine Gaul, Illyricum, and the province oi Narbo, or simply provincia, with three legions, for a term of five years. Caesar had now attained his object.
